                        <accMat>
                            <p>The old cover (belonging to this fragment?) says: <q xml:lang="is">Þetta fragmentum fan<expan>n</expan> eg anno <date>1725</date>.
                                in<expan>n</expan>ani hryggnu<expan>m</expan> ä Iislendsku
                                kvere, er ätt hafde Sr Þord<expan>ur</expan> Jonsson i Hitardal,
                                <expan>og</expan> epter han<expan>n</expan> Þorsteinn
                                Þordarson. Kvered var in<expan>n</expan>saumadad forlage
                                Þ<expan>or</expan>steins Þordarsonar, þvi
                                in<expan>n</expan>ani bandinu voru .2. sendibref til Þorsteins
                                dat. 1673. <expan>og</expan> 76] anno <date>1676</date>. eda
                                sidar. feck eg þ<expan>ad</expan> af <name type="person" key="GudTho006">Gudmunde Þorleifssyne</name> ä Eyre, en<expan>n</expan>
                                h<expan>an</expan>n hafde feinged þ<expan>ad</expan> ä
                                Skarde, ad eg þykizt vist vita</q>
                     </p>
                        </accMat>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1225" notAfter="1250" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>Written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>. <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name> dated it <origDate>to the
                                    first half of the thirteenth century</origDate>, (<bibl>
                                    <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">KKKat</ref>
                                </bibl>) whereas <name type="person" key="GusLin001">Gustav
                                    Lindblad</name> dated it more precisely <origDate notBefore="1225" notAfter="1250" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">the second quarter of the thirteenth
                                    century</origDate> (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary" target="Lindblad1952">Lindblad 1952</ref>, p.
                                92</bibl>).</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The leaf was used as cover for a small book that belonged to the
                                Priest <name type="person" key="ThoJon006">Þórður Jónsson</name> of
                                    <name type="place">Hítardalur</name> and later to <name type="person" key="ThoTho016">Þorsteinn Þórðarson</name>. After
                                that it belonged to some people from <name type="place">Skarð,
                                    Skarðsströnd</name>, who gave it to<name type="person" key="GudTho006"> Guðmundur Þorleifsson</name>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>
                        <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> got the
                                leaf from <name type="person" key="GudTho006">Guðmundur
                                    Þorleifsson</name>. On the old cover (belonging to this
                                fragment?) Árni writes: <q xml:lang="is">Þetta fragmentum
                                        fan<expan>n</expan> eg anno <date>1725</date>.
                                        in<expan>n</expan>ani hryggnu<expan>m</expan> ä Iislendsku
                                    kvere, er ätt hafde Sr Þord<expan>ur</expan> Jonsson i Hitardal,
                                        <expan>og</expan> epter han<expan>n</expan> Þorsteinn
                                    Þordarson. Kvered var in<expan>n</expan>saumadad forlage
                                        Þ<expan>or</expan>steins Þordarsonar, þvi
                                    in<expan>n</expan>ani bandinu voru .2. sendibref til Þorsteins
                                    dat. 1673. <expan>og</expan> 76] anno <date>1676</date>. eda
                                    sidar. feck eg þ<expan>ad</expan> af <name type="person" key="GudTho006">Gudmunde Þorleifssyne</name> ä Eyre,
                                        en<expan>n</expan> h<expan>an</expan>n hafde feinged
                                        þ<expan>ad</expan> ä Skarde, ad eg þykizt vist vita</q>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
